infotext.p1: The application has been developed by the Finnish Museum of Natural History Luomus in the project Flying Squirrel LIFE which is coordinated by Mets√§hallitus Parks & Wildlife Finland. The EU-funded project aims to improve conservation of the flying squirrel in the EU by improving viable habitat networks in the future.

instructions.1: Start recording without prestored location OR select the location, which was established at Species.fi (https://laji.fi/en/project/MHL.45/about ).
instructions.2: Liituri starts GPS tracking automatically and stores your track.
instructions.3: Point in the map, where you want to add an observation and select the observation type from the selection that becomes visible.
instructions.4: Add new observations along the trail.
instructions.5: Stop the observation event by touching the red square at the top right corner of the screen and you will be taken to the homepage.
instructions.6: At the bottom of the homepage, you will find the list of your unsaved events, which can be checked, amended and stored in to FinBIF data warehouse.
instructions.7: The authorised users of Flying squirrel monitoring service at Species.fi, may enrich the data stored in Liituri.
instructions.intro: Liituri is an observation service designed for recoding Flying squirrel observations in the field.
instructions.mobilevihko.intro: Save nature observations from all taxon groups to species.fi database.
